TopFeatures.FeatureShortText: Standard Single Private Room
TopFeatures.FeatureDescription: Room rent limit is the maximum allowed room category and cost of room per day
TopFeatures.FeatureImportance: Room rent limit is the maximum amount per day cost allowed by the insurer. Related expenses, such as doctor consultation etc. are paid in proportion to the room rent limit.  Look out for plans with No Room Rent limit

TopFeatures.FeatureName: Increase in Sum Insured offered by insurance companies if the insured person has not made a single claim during the previous year
TopFeatures.FeatureText: Rs 7.5 lakh per year and up to maximum of additional Rs 15 lakh. In case of a claim, the no claim bonus will reduce by Rs 7.5 lakh
TopFeatures.FeatureShortText: Rs 7.5 lakh per year and up to maximum of additional Rs 15 lakh. In case of a claim, the no claim bonus will reduce by Rs 7.5 lakh
TopFeatures.FeatureDescription: This is a reward from the insurer for not claiming during a policy year. This increases your sum insured without additional cost
TopFeatures.FeatureImportance: No Claim Bonus is the reward for not making a claim. Depending on plan, Insurer adds a 5%-100% bonus to the Sum Insured at no extra premium.

TopFeatures.FeatureName: Restoration of the sum insured by insurance companies if the base sum insured (plus any no claim bonus) gets exhausted in an year. Usually for an unrelated illness
TopFeatures.FeatureText: Rs 15 lakh once in a year; for unrelated illness
TopFeatures.FeatureShortText: Rs 15 lakh once in a year; for unrelated illness
TopFeatures.FeatureDescription: If you use up your entire cover amount, it will be fully restored for your next claim. This restored amount doesnt include no claim bonus
TopFeatures.FeatureImportance: Very useful feature, in case the sum Insured gets exhausted in a year due to multiple claims or a large claim. Insurer restores the sum insured to provide continued coverage to policyholders.
TopFeatures.FeatureCrispShortText: Restoration of cover once a year

TopFeatures.FeatureName: Medical Expenses associated with hospitalization of the insured person for the delivery of a child
TopFeatures.FeatureText: Up to Rs 2 lakh; after 4 years
TopFeatures.FeatureShortText: Up to Rs 2 lakh; after 4 years
TopFeatures.FeatureDescription: This covers the cost of maternity and related expenses including hospitalization, delivery, and doctor fees It also covers the expenses for your newborn for a fixed period
TopFeatures.FeatureImportance: Covers for expenses incurred on child delivery, pre and post-natal expenses are covered. Suitable for couples planning or expecting a child. Do check the waiting periods in your plan.
